name: Ultimate Warrior
description:
follow me on Instagram, Youtube and my website.

Ultimate Warrior

First of all, you can just use the prompt "ultimate warrior" in most SD 1.5 models and get something that looks half decent, but I wanted more control and consistency between models, without conflicting with any known styles.

The result was something far more useful and flexible than I expected, this textual inversion will let you turn anyone you want into an over-the-top flamboyant wrestler, complete with muscles and facepaint and wild hair.

Suggested Weight: 0.6-1.2 (this is where the embedding shines imo, you can dial it up or down as much as you need, depending on how well it's mixing with the other subject)

Suggested prompts

  • promotional photo of (person:1.0) as (u1t1m4t3w4rr10r:1.0)

  • photo of (woman:1.0) as (female u1t1m4t3w4rr10r:1.0)

  • promotional photo of (person:1.0) as (u1t1m4t3w4rr10r:1.0), (facepaint:0.6)

Training

  • trained on ~10 images

  • Learning Rate: 0.005:1000, 0.001:2000, 0.0001:5000, 0.00005

  • Batch Size: 1

  • Gradient Steps: 1
